    {
      "id": "story-1a",
      "kind": "r3f-scene",
      "durationInFrames": 420,
      "narration": "First, Anthropic shipped Opus 4.7 to general availability. The headline number: an eighteen-percent lift on SWE-bench Verified over last month's 4.6, with the biggest jumps on multi-step tasks.",
      "params": {
        "background": "#000000",
        "motionProfile": "asmr",
        "camera": { "position": [0, 0, 10], "fov": 38 },
        "primitives": [
          { "primitive": "r3f.count-up-bar", "params": { "target": 18, "unit": "%", "label": "SWE-bench lift", "barColor": "#4de0ff" } }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "story-1b",
      "kind": "r3f-scene",
      "durationInFrames": 600,
      "narration": "The gain isn't benchmark noise. In agentic coding, 4.7 holds a plan across dozens of tool calls without drift, where 4.6 lost the thread around call twelve. If you loop Claude inside a coding agent in production, your ceiling just moved. The upgrade is a one-line model swap.",
      "params": {
        "background": "#000000",
        "motionProfile": "asmr",
        "camera": { "position": [0, 0, 10], "fov": 38 },
        "primitives": [
          { "primitive": "r3f.orbiting-tags", "params": { "tags": ["LONG-HORIZON", "AGENTIC", "CODING"], "radius": 2.8, "tagSize": 0.42, "color": "#1e4e6e", "textColor": "#bfe9ff" } }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "story-2a",
      "kind": "r3f-scene",
      "durationInFrames": 420,
      "narration": "Second, Alibaba's Qwen team dropped Qwen 3.7 under an open-weights license. Coming off 3.6, the step up is a fresh seventy-two-billion-parameter checkpoint with a new training mix and a sharper long-context recipe.",
      "params": {
        "background": "#000000",
        "motionProfile": "asmr",
        "camera": { "position": [0, 0, 10], "fov": 38 },
        "primitives": [
          { "primitive": "r3f.versus-cards", "params": { "left": { "label": "Qwen 3.6" }, "right": { "label": "Qwen 3.7" } } }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "story-2b",
      "kind": "r3f-scene",
      "durationInFrames": 540,
      "narration": "One-twenty-eight K context, open weights, Apache-2 license. If your roadmap includes a regulated customer who can't send data to a closed API, this is the first 2026 drop that clears the bar on all three fronts. Expect Llama to answer within a month.",
      "params": {
        "background": "#000000",
        "motionProfile": "asmr",
        "camera": { "position": [0, 0, 10], "fov": 38 },
        "primitives": [
          { "primitive": "r3f.number-sculpture", "params": { "value": 72, "unit": "B", "label": "parameters", "fontSize": 2.4 } }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "outro",
      "kind": "r3f-scene",
      "durationInFrames": 660,
      "narration": "Two moves, one thread. The frontier is compressing, and the open-weights tier just caught up on the benchmarks that matter for real applications. The watch list: Mistral. They've been quiet since February. If they drop their own open-weights refresh by Friday, the closed-source moat thins again. See you tomorrow.",
      "captions": [],
